block content

  // Article Hero
  header.bg-primary.text-white.py-5(style="margin-top: 76px;")
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8
          nav(aria-label="breadcrumb")
            ol.breadcrumb.mb-3
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/") Home
              li.breadcrumb-item
                a.text-white-50(href="/blog.html") Blog
              li.breadcrumb-item.active.text-white(aria-current="page") AA & NA Meetings
          h1.display-5.fw-bold AA &amp; NA Meetings in Spokane, WA – Complete Guide
          p.lead.mt-3.text-white-75 Find meeting times, locations, and formats across every Spokane neighborhood.
          .small.text-white-50.mt-2
            i.bi.bi-calendar3.me-1
            | March 2025 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
            i.bi.bi-clock.me-1
            | 5 min read

  // Article Body
  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8

          // What is AA/NA
          h2.mt-5 What Are AA and NA Meetings?
          p
            | Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) and Narcotics Anonymous (NA) are free, peer-led support groups for people in recovery from alcohol and drug addiction. Meetings are open to anyone at any stage of recovery — no appointment or commitment required.
          p
            | Both programs follow a 12-step model built on fellowship, personal accountability, and spiritual (not religious) growth. AA focuses on alcohol; NA focuses on all substances. Many people attend both.

          // How to Find a Meeting
          h2.mt-5 How to Find an AA or NA Meeting in Spokane
          p Spokane has a robust recovery community with dozens of meetings held every day of the week. Here's how to find one:
          ul
            li
              strong AA Spokane District:
              |  Visit &nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.aa-eastern-wa.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener") aa-eastern-wa.org
              |  for a full searchable meeting schedule.
            li
              strong NA Inland Northwest:
              |  Visit &nbsp;
              a(href="https://www.inlandnorthwestna.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener") inlandnorthwestna.org
              |  for NA meeting listings in Spokane and surrounding areas.
            li
              strong SAMHSA Helpline:
              |  Call &nbsp;
              strong 1-800-662-4357
              |  (free, confidential) for local referral to meetings and treatment.

          // Meetings by Neighborhood
          h2.mt-5 AA &amp; NA Meetings by Spokane Neighborhood

          h3.h5.mt-4
            i.bi.bi-geo-alt-fill.text-primary.me-2
            | South Hill
          p South Hill hosts several daily meetings at local churches and community centers. Popular formats include Big Book study, speaker meetings, and open discussion.
          ul
            li Holy Family Church – Monday/Wednesday/Friday evenings
            li South Hill Community Center – Daily noon meetings
            li St. John's Cathedral – Saturday and Sunday morning meetings

          h3.h5.mt-4
            i.bi.bi-geo-alt-fill.text-primary.me-2
            | North Spokane
          p North Spokane has a strong AA presence with multiple early morning and evening options throughout the week.
          ul
            li First Presbyterian Church – Monday through Saturday mornings
            li North Side Community Hall – Tuesday and Thursday evenings
            li Shadle Park area – Weekend speaker meetings

          h3.h5.mt-4
            i.bi.bi-geo-alt-fill.text-primary.me-2
            | Spokane Valley
          p Spokane Valley offers accessible meeting locations near Liberty Lake and the Valley corridor.
          ul
            li Valley 12-Step Club – Daily meetings (multiple formats)
            li Liberty Lake Community Church – Wednesday and Friday evenings
            li Greenacres area – Weekend Big Book meetings

          // Tips for First-Timers
          h2.mt-5 Tips for First-Timers
          .row.gx-3.gy-3.mt-1
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-check-circle-fill.text-success.me-2
                    | You don't have to speak
                  p.small.mb-0 First-timers can simply listen. Introduce yourself only if you feel comfortable.
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-check-circle-fill.text-success.me-2
                    | Meetings are confidential
                  p.small.mb-0 What's shared in the room stays in the room.
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-check-circle-fill.text-success.me-2
                    | Try a few different ones
                  p.small.mb-0 Each meeting has its own personality. Don't judge all meetings by one.
            .col-md-6
              .card.border-0.shadow-sm.h-100(style="border-radius: 10px;")
                .card-body
                  h6.fw-bold
                    i.bi.bi-check-circle-fill.text-success.me-2
                    | It's free, always
                  p.small.mb-0 AA and NA never charge for attendance. A small voluntary donation is sometimes passed.

          // Internal Links CTA
          .row.g-3.mt-5.mb-4
            .col-12
              h4 Ready for your next step?
            .col-md-6
              a.btn.btn-primary.w-100(href="/sponsor-finder.html")
                i.bi.bi-person-heart.me-2
                | Find a Sponsor in Spokane
            .col-md-6
              a.btn.btn-outline-primary.w-100(href="/resource-directory.html" onclick="gtag('event', 'resources_click', {event_category: 'engagement', event_label: 'blog_post_footer'})")
                i.bi.bi-list-ul.me-2
                | Browse All Recovery Resources
